choices.text: Yes, there are several code smells in this code. The first is the repeated element which is the h:form tag. This tag should only be used once in a page, and is being used twice in this code. The second code smell is the use of inline styling. Inline styling should be avoided as it makes the code harder to read and maintain, and makes it less portable. The third code smell is the use of multiple HTML namespaces. Too many HTML namespaces can make the code less maintainable and more difficult to read. The fourth code smell is the lack of structure in the CSS style rules. The CSS style rules are haphazardly scattered throughout the code, making it difficult to find and adjust when needed. Finally, there is the lack of consistency in the naming of elements. Variable names, class names, and ids are all randomly named, and lack a consistent naming structure.
